TY  - JOUR
T1  - Effects of Leadership Style and Followers' Cultural Orientation on Performance in Group and Individual Task Conditions
AU  - Jung, Dong I.
AU  - Avolio, Bruce J.
Y1  - 1999/04/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/257093
DO  - 10.5465/257093
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 208
EP  - 218
VL  - 42
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We manipulated transformational and transactional leadership styles and compared them in individual and group task conditions to determine whether they had different impacts on individualists and collectivists performing a brainstorming task. Results showed that collectivists with a transformational leader generated more ideas, but individualists generated more ideas with a transactional leader. Group performance was generally higher than that of individuals working alone. However, contrary to expectations, collectivists generated more ideas that required fundamental organizational changes when working alone.
AB  - We manipulated transformational and transactional leadership styles and compared them in individual and group task conditions to determine whether they had different impacts on individualists and collectivists performing a brainstorming task. Results showed that collectivists with a transformational leader generated more ideas, but individualists generated more ideas with a transactional leader. Group performance was generally higher than that of individuals working alone. However, contrary to expectations, collectivists generated more ideas that required fundamental organizational changes when working alone.
