TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to the Bottom Line: Humor as a Moderator of Leadership Style Effects
AU  - Avolio, Bruce J.
AU  - Howell, Jane M.
AU  - Sosik, John J.
Y1  - 1999/04/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/257094
DO  - 10.5465/257094
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 219
EP  - 227
VL  - 42
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In this study, we examined the links between leadership style, the use of humor, and two measures of performance. Results indicated that leadership style was moderated by the use of humor in its relationship with individual and unit-level performance. Implications for further research on the use of humor by leaders are discussed.
AB  - In this study, we examined the links between leadership style, the use of humor, and two measures of performance. Results indicated that leadership style was moderated by the use of humor in its relationship with individual and unit-level performance. Implications for further research on the use of humor by leaders are discussed.
